HEADWORD: Mundificant
<hw>Mun*dif"i*cant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>mundificans</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>mundificare</ets> to make clean,
fr. <ets>mundus</ets> clean + <ets>-ficare</ets> (in comp.) to make. See
<er>-fy</er>.]</ety> <def>Serving to cleanse and heal.</def> --
<def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>A mundificant ointment or
plaster.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
